# ClockDomainCrew

Chisel-based hardware designs following chiselware standards.

## Modules

### nfmac10g - 10 Gigabit Ethernet MAC

Located in `modules/nfmac10g/`

**Components:**
- XGMII interface
- AXI Stream conversion
- Transmit/Receive logic
- Flow control (pause frames)

## Building
```bash
# Compile all modules
sbt compile

# Compile specific module
sbt "project nfmac10g" compile
```

## Testing
```bash
# Run all tests
sbt test

# Test specific module
sbt "project nfmac10g" test
```

## Generating Verilog
```bash
sbt "project nfmac10g" "runMain org.chiselware.cores.o01.t001.nfmac10g.NfMac10gVerilog"
```

## Project Structure
ClockDomainCrew/
├── build.sbt                 # Root build configuration
├── docs/                     # Project documentation
├── modules/                  # Hardware modules
│   └── nfmac10g/            # 10G MAC module
│       ├── docs/            # Module documentation
│       └── src/             # Module source
│           ├── main/scala/  # Chisel sources
│           └── test/scala/  # ChiselTest tests
└── project/                 # SBT configuration

## Documentation

- Module documentation: `modules/nfmac10g/docs/user-guide/`
- Verification: `docs/verification-compliance/`